15/05/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- Ten children, including a four-month old baby, were rushed to hospital on Thursday (May 14th) after police accidentally fired a tear gas canister into a school in the town of Altinsehir, near Istanbul. It happened during a clash between police and owners of an illegal building that authorities want to tear down near the school. Police say the tear gas canister landed in the school by mistake. (AP, Hurriyet, NTV, ITAR-TASS - 14/05/09) 
